      <hr class="center-ball">
      <p class='web-pro-text'>
        Majority of individuals over the age of 65 years suffer from at least two chronic
degenerative diseases- neurodegeneration, cardiovascular disease, diabetes, cancer etc.
These chronic diseases of the elderly consume an increasingly large fraction of our health care
costs and rob individuals of their independence and quality of life. The Gurkar lab is interested
in defining the molecular mechanisms that drive aging in response to DNA damage, which
accumulates in all of us over time.
      </p>
